==Construction==
The Sizewell C project is expected to take between nine and twelve years to construct and commission.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Sizwell C Environmental, Social and Governance Commitments |url=https://www.sizewellc.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/03/2022-szc-esg-brochure.pdf |page=2}}</ref> EDF expects significant time and cost savings compared to the near-identical sister plant, Hinkley Point C.{{citation needed|date=May 2022}} The projected construction cost of £20{{nbsp}}billion (including "expected inflation and contingencies") for Sizewell C in the 2020 development consent submission<ref name=":1">{{cite web |url=https://infrastructure.planninginspectorate.gov.uk/wp-content/ipc/uploads/projects/EN010012/EN010012-001678-SZC_Bk4_4.2_Funding_Statement.pdf |title=The Sizewell C Project. 4.2 Funding Statement |date=May 2020 |publisher=EDF Energy |access-date=22 December 2022}}</ref> is 25% higher than the £16{{nbsp}}billion (2012 prices) projected for Hinkley Point C during the planning process.<ref>{{Cite web |title=Hinkley Point C contract terms - World Nuclear News |url=https://www.world-nuclear-news.org/np-hinkley-point-c-contract-terms-08101401.html |access-date=2024-08-08 |website=www.world-nuclear-news.org}}</ref> Note that the £20{{nbsp}}billion figure was calculated by inflation adjusting 80% of the cost estimate of Hinkley Point C at that time.<ref name=":0">{{Cite news |last1=Thomas |first1=Nathalie |last2=Mancini |first2=Donato Paolo |date=2020-06-25 |title=Cost of new Sizewell C nuclear plant put at £20bn |work=Financial Times |url=https://www.ft.com/content/77c209f7-6d18-4609-ac3c-77d1b5b82b34 |access-date=2021-12-29 |archive-date=29 December 2021 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20211229220023/https://www.ft.com/content/77c209f7-6d18-4609-ac3c-77d1b5b82b34 |url-status=live}}</ref>

